40|$|THE LEGAL FRAME THAT REGULATES DEFECTIVE <b>MERGERS</b> <b>AND</b> <b>SCISSIONS</b> OF PUBLIC COMPANIES (A. E.) HAS BEEN ENACTED IN COMPLIANCE TO THE 3 RD AND 6 TH E. E. C. COUNCILDIRECTIVES. THE SIGNIFICANCE OF THIS LEGISLATION IS NOTEWORTHY, CONSIDERING THAT <b>MERGERS</b> <b>AND</b> <b>SCISSIONS</b> ARE IMPORTANT MEANS FOR THE CONCENTRATION OF GREEKENTERPRISES AND ALSO, BECAUSE THE PERPLEXITY OF THE PROCEDURE SET FORTH BY THE COMPANY LAW FAVOURS THE APPEARANCE OF DEFECTS. THE COUNCIL DIRECTIVES HAVE INTRODUCED TWO SYSTEMS OF HANDLING A DEFECTIVE MERGER OR SCISSION. PRINCIPAL AIM OF BOTH SYSTEMS IS LAW AND TRANSACTIONS' SECURITY. THE FIRST OF THESE SYSTEMS ALLOWS SHAREHOLDERS AND THIRD PARTIES TO HOLD DIRECTORS LIABLE FOR ANY FAULT COMMITED, BUT NOT TO FILE AN ACTION FOR THE ANNULMENT OF THE DEFECTIVE MERGER OR SCISSION. THE SECOND SYSTEM WHICH HAS BEEN ADOPTED BY THE GREEK LEGISLATION PRESCRIBES THE POSSIBILITY OF A NULLIFYING ACTION. THE STUDY OF THE LEGALFRAME WHICH RULES DEFECTIVE <b>MERGERS</b> <b>AND</b> <b>SCISSIONS</b> INCLUDES THE GROUNDS, PROCEDURE AND CONSEQUENCES FOR THE ANNULMENT. PURPOSE OF THIS STUDY IS THE LIMITATION THROUGH INTERPRETATION OF THE GROUNDS AND OF THE CONSEQUENCES OF THE ANNULMENT, DUE TO THE PRACTICAL DIFFICULTIES AROSEN BY THE NULLIFYING JUDGEMENT. HENCE, THE ANNULMENT MUST BE CONSIDERED AS AN "ULTIMUM REMEDIUM", WHICH MUST BE DECLARED ONLY IF THE DEFECTS INVOKED ARE ABSOLUTELY INCURABLE. (ABSTRACTTRUNCATED) ...|$|E
