40|$|The study {{examined}} the attitude and reactions of bank workers to <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions in the industry, investigated methods used to curb redundancies and joblessness arising from <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions, and examined the different strategies employed by banks involved in <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions to manage employment issues in the industry. Primary and secondary data were used for this study; and questionnaires were administered to 300 employees of 8 purposively selected banks of the 24 post-consolidated banks and in-depth interviews conducted on human resources Managers of the 8 selected banks. Data collected were analyzed using descriptive statistics. The results also showed that banks workers’ attitudes and reactions are positive towards <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions, and that training and re-training of workers, job re-designing, and intra and inter branches transfers, were various methods used to curb redundancies and job loss. Finally, {{the results showed that}} provision of support services, provision and prompt payment of severance package, ceiling on voluntary resignation are strategies adopted by these banks to address employment issues arising from <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisition. The study concluded that as much as the positive contributions of <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions in achieving organizational effectiveness, profit maximization, increase in productivity, career opportunities, better job opportunities, the associated job losses and redundancies, which are aftermath of <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition, are issues that could not be ignored if successful <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions would be achieved...|$|R
40|$|Composition of <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> {{acquisition}} risk {{of agricultural}} manufacturing enterprises in China is analyzed, which is mainly strategic risk, external risk, transaction risk and integrated risk. And {{there are a}} total of 16 specific sources of risk. Concrete assessment methods for <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition risk of agricultural manufacturing enterprises are introduced. Firstly, set up the risk factor sets at first and second layers <b>and</b> divide <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition risk into 5 layers; establish risk assessment matrix according to the score by expert group. Secondly, determine the weights of the various risk factors by the ideology of information entropy. Finally, find out the subordinated vector of risk factor, construct risk assessment matrix, calculate the second grade risk assessment vector and conduct risk assessment. Taking an agricultural manufacturing enterprise as an example, fuzzy mathematics method is used to conduct risk assessment on its <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition project. Result shows that the overall risk of <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition project is relatively low, <b>and</b> <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition can be implemented. <b>Merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition risk assessment based on fuzzy mathematics has made the assessment result more objective and reliable, so as to provide a reasonable reference for the scientific decision-making of agricultural manufacturing enterprises in China. <b>Merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition risk, Information entropy, Risk control, China, Industrial Organization, Risk and Uncertainty,...|$|R
40|$|For {{the past}} years the {{takeover}} technique <b>and</b> <b>merger</b> defense {{have been paid}} special attention and have been closely studied. However, the inside experience in newly merged organizations, the challenges that management faces and the solutions for problems often remain uncovered. Most importantly, if the management does not put efforts, the merger {{is not going to}} work. This study is an attempt to present a view to an insight of managing in a post-merger/ post-acquisition situation in a service enterprise. The study includes the following aspects: <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions: What causes companies to merge? The Process of Merging/Acquiring. Reasons for <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions. History of <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions. Current situation in <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions market: in general, <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions in Service Industry, Banking Industry, Hotel Industry. <b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> Acquisitions practice in Marriott International. Employee satisfaction level in a post-merged situation and its effects. Managing and maintaining employee satisfaction in a post-merged environment...|$|R
