40|$|With the {{liberalization}} of economy and globalization, business communications among nations has become more frequently. The same is true as the cooperation and competition between financial institutions from different countries. Under such condition, there is a driving trend of large-scale <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions (M&A) activities worldwide. China, {{as one of the}} outstanding representatives of emerging economies, has achieved high-speed in economic growth. Many commercial banks of China have set about the cross-border <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions not only to promote the international influence but also to increase their profitability and efficiency. This paper uses the Stochastic Frontier Analysis (SFA) model to examine the relationships between <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions and cost efficiency in Chinese bank industry. According to the announcement time of <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions, the two groups that pre <b>and</b> post <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions groups are built. The changed value of cost efficiency in the two groups may reflect the effect of <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions. The main finding of this paper suggests that the <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions have significant positive effect on cost efficiency of Chinese banks. Key words: Cross-border M&A, Chinese bank industry, SF...|$|R
40|$|<b>Mergers</b> <b>and</b> {{acquisitions}} {{have had}} a significant impact on the banking industry in Nigeria and around the world, over the last decade. As a result, many bank employees have experienced numerous psychological effects of <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisition. Acquisition is often seen to have negative impacts on employee's behaviour, resulting in counter productive practices, absenteeism, low morale and job dissatisfaction. This paper studied the effects of <b>merger</b> <b>and</b> acquisition on the morale and psychology of employees in the Nigerian banking sector and how it affects employee's productivity. It identified the different stages in <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisition and also the problems that may emerge at each stage of <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisition integration process. The paper observed that various factors relate to pre <b>and</b> post <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisition stages among which communication seems to be the most vital. The paper therefore suggests that open, timely, and accurate communication with employees may effectively reduce the negative psychological and behavioural consequences, thereby reducing employee's anxiety, uncertainty, confusion, rumour activity and labour turnover. psychological effects; <b>mergers</b> <b>and</b> acquisitions; M&A; bank employees; banks; productivity; Nigeria; banking industry; employee behaviour; employee morale; communication. ...|$|R
